<div type="edition" xml:lang="tam-Latn" rendition="class:tamil maturity:vernacular">

<p>
<lb n="1"/><hi rend="grantha">svasti śrī</hi> <supplied reason="undefined"><g ref="sym:doubleBar" type="punctuation">.</g></supplied> cālai kalamaṟutta kovirā<hi rend="grantha">ja</hi>rā<hi rend="grantha">ja</hi>kecaripa<hi rend="grantha">nma</hi> ṟki yāṇṭu <num value="10"><g type="numeral">10</g></num><g ref="sym:dash" type="punctuation"/>Āvatu Oymāṉāṭṭuk kiṭakkai
<lb n="2" break="no"/>ñāṭṭuk kiṭaṅkil tiruttiṇṭī<hi rend="grantha">śva</hi> ra<hi rend="grantha">de</hi> varkku vīṇaivācippāṉukkum Uṭaṉpāṭuvā ṉoruvanukkuṅ
<lb n="3"/>kiṭaṅkiṟ kaṭampūḻāṉ tīrtta nātittan muruṅkaippākkattil tirutti vaiytta nilam veppañceṟuviṉ teṟkiṟ kaṇṇāṟu varavai
<lb n="4"/>Aiñcināṟ kuḻi Āyirattaiññūṟu kuḻiyum pāṭikāppānpaṭṭikkuk kiḻakkum vaṭakku maikkaraikkut teṟku Aṟunūṟu kuḻiyūm pūḷiyaṅko
<lb n="5" break="no"/>llaiyil tirttaneṉṟu tiruttina ceṟu kuḻi Eṇṇūṟṟorupatu kuḻiyum Āka kuḻi Iraṇṭāyirattut toḷḷāyirattorupatu kuḻiyūm tirutti vīṇaivācippāṉuk
<lb n="6" break="no"/>kum Uṭaṉpāṭuvā ṉoruvanukkum cantirātittavaṟ ti<supplied reason="omitted">r</supplied>ttaṉāccan tirutti vaittatu<note n="66-2">In this inscription the secondary <hi rend="italic">i</hi>-symbol has been wrongly used for <hi rend="italic">i</hi> in many places.</note><g ref="sym:doubleBar" type="punctuation">.</g><g ref="sym:dash-long" type="punctuation">.</g>
</p>

